   Billionaire motorcycle enthusiast Malcolm
Forbes will be revving up the Harley-Davidson for a 50-mile charity
ride.
   The 70-year-old publisher has agreed to ride in the Syria Motor
Corps Fall Poker Run Sept. 24, said Don Garson, a spokesman for
Forbes Inc. in New York.
   Bikers in the run, held to raise money for the Shrine Hospital in
