<HEAD>With PM-Senate-FSX</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 66-34 roll call by which the Senate
sustained President Bush's veto of legislation placing restrictions
on a joint fighter production agreement between the United States
and Japan.
   On this vote, a yes vote was a vote to override the veto while a
no vote was a vote to sustain it. A two-thirds majority of the 100
senators was required to override the veto.
   Voting yes were 54 Democrats and 12 Republicans.
   Voting no were 1 Democrat and 33 Republicans.
