<FIRST>r i PM-China-Blast     09-14 0131</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-China-Blast,0134</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Killed In Bus Explosion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three people were killed and 20 injured in an
explosion in a bus in Nanning, capital of southern China's Guangxi
province, an official report said today.
   The China News Service said the explosion, which occurred as the
bus pulled up at a stop at 7:10 p.m. Sunday, blasted open the front
door of the bus and shattered window glass.
   It said two people died at the scene. Another person died while
being taken to a hospital.
   The report said dozens of passenger crawled out of the bus
through its windows and 20 were injured. It did not say how many
were on the bus at the time of the explosion.
   The report did not give the cause of the blast.
</TEXT>
