<HEAD>Cocaine Found in Duct of Eastern Airlines Plane</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Airport guards found 11 pounds of
cocaine in the air conditioning duct of an Eastern Airlines plane
while conducting a routine search, authorities said Thursday.
   The Boeing 727 plane arrived in Caracas on Wednesday night from
Miami and the drug was found a few hours later, airport authorities
said.
   Venezuelan national guards routinely search Eastern flights since
small quantities of drugs have been found on the carrier's planes at
least six times in the past few months, they said.
   The plane returned to Miami on the regular Thursday morning
flight.
