<FIRST>r w AM-FlagBook     09-14 0195</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Flag Book,200</SECOND>
<HEAD>New Flag Book Rolls Off Government Press</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Our Flag,'' a book on the history and care of
the U.S. flag, is rolling off government presses after being out of
print for more than a decade, lawmakers said Thursday.
   ``It is back by popular demand,'' said Sen. Wendell H. Ford,
D-Ky., chairman of the Joint Committee on Printing.
   Congress last year approved a resolution to revise the 52-page
book and print nearly 300,000 copies. They will be given to each
lawmaker for free distribution to constituents and many will be sold
through the Government Printing Office.
   Ford said the book went out of print because there was no demand
for it.
   ``But now we're getting a lot of requests for it,'' Ford said.
``There was a lot of enthusiasm for the flag built around political
campaigns.''
   He said Sen. William V. Roth, R-Del., got 10,000 requests.
   Rep. Frank Annunzio, D-Ill., vice chairman of the committee, said
Congress acted a year ago to put the book back in print and that the
recent Supreme Court ruling striking down a Texas law prohibiting
flag desecration had no bearing on the decision.
</TEXT>
