<FIRST>r a AM-People SUB a0637 09-14 0264</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People, SUB, a0637,0269</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds: ADDS 2 grafs to MURPHREESBORO, Tenn.-dated item to UPDATE with
comment from Zsa Zsa Gabor.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MURFREESBORO, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   As if she didn't have enough trouble,
actress Zsa Zsa Gabor is being accused of skipping out on a $75 bill
for hair styling she received while attending a horse show two weeks
ago.
   Hair salon operator Jerry Perry said he styled Ms. Gabor's hair
three times while she attended the Tennessee Walking Horse National
Celebration in nearby Shelbyville.
   The actress is on trial in Beverly Hills, Calif., charged with
battery on a police officer, disobeying a police officer, driving
with an expired license, having expired car registration and having
an open bottle of liquor in her car.
   Perry said he tried three times to get the actress to pay, but
she delayed him and finally said the horse show would cover the cost.
   ``She said the Celebration people would take care of the bill,
but I had been told by Celebration people they would not pay the
bill, but you can not stand and argue with Zsa Zsa,'' he said
Wednesday.
   Brenda Gibson, a spokeswoman for the annual horse show, said the
bill will be forwarded to Ms. Gabor.
   Asked about Jerry Perry's disputed bill, Miss Gabor said from Los
Angeles: ``I don't know who the hell you're talking about. I didn't
have a hairdresser in Nashville. I was on my horse.''
   Her husband, Prince Frederick von Anhalt, Germany's Duke of
Saxony, then injected this comment: ``She can't get her hair done
for $75. Her hairdresser costs $350.''
</TEXT>
