<HEAD>Roy Disney Buys Irish Castle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CORK, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Roy Disney, nephew of the late Walt Disney,
has bought Coolmaine Castle in Ireland as a home and possible base
for his ocean yacht racing, Sotheby's International Realty said
Thursday.
   ``The sale figure was in the region of the asking price of
750,000 pounds ($1.16 million),'' said Amanda Blackmore, spokeswoman
for Sotheby's.
   The 18th-century battlemented castle was sold by American movie
cameraman Bob Willoughby, she said. It is in 40 acres of countryside
overlooking Courtmacsherry Bay near Kinsale on the south Irish coast.
   Disney owns TV stations in Honolulu; Santa Barbara, Calif.; and
Lexington, Ky.; and 14 radio stations. He is chairman of Shamrock
Holdings Inc. of Burbank, Calif., which owns 4 million shares in
Walt Disney Co.
