<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-BoatPeople     09-14 0157</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Boat People,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>China Says It Will Take Back Chinese Refugees</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chinese officials said Thursday they will accept
back all Chinese citizens who entered Japan in recent weeks by
posing as Vietnamese boat people.
   Foreign Ministry spokesman Li Zhaoxing said China has asked Japan
for details on 660 suspected Chinese held in detention centers for
Vietnamese refugees.
   Li said Japan has already provided the names of 39 people
believed to be Chinese citizens.
   He said China would investigate all the cases. ``If it is
verified that they are Chinese, China will accept repatriation,'' he
said.
   Toshio Tsunozaki, director of Japan's Foreign Ministry Human
Rights and Refugee Division, said Tuesday that interviews with the
Chinese showed they came to Japan for economic, not political
reasons.
   Tsunozaki said he hoped the Chinese would not be harshly punished
when they go home.
   Li did not comment on whether they would face legal charges when
they return.
</TEXT>
