<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
211,763 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
173,020, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago, in
which 233,750 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 140,528 cars this week,
compared with 108,175 a week ago and 145,386 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 71,235,
compared with last week's 64,845 and last year's 88,364.
   Canadian automakers were to build 20,883 cars this week, up from
15,047 a week ago and from last year's 20,701.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 20,920, compared
with 17,045 a week ago and 21,690 in the same week last year.
