<FIRST>r f AM-Britain-Maxwell     09-14 0216</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Britain-Maxwell,0226</SECOND>
<HEAD>Maxwell Says He's on The Brink of Buying North American Publisher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert Maxwell, chairman of Maxwell Communications
Corp. PLC, said Thursday his company was on the verge of acquiring a
medium-sized educational publishing business and an information
services business in North America.
   Maxwell, speaking at the company's annual meeting, said the
publishing concern also expects to soon acquire some magazine,
exhibition and company information services businesses.
   Shareholders on Thursday approved an increase in the company's
borrowing power to 2.8 billion pounds, or about $4.4 billion, up
from 2 billion pounds, or $3.1 billion.
   Maxwell announced that Maxwell Communications has arranged a $3
billion credit facility with several banks to replace its existing
borrowings.
   Maxwell acquired the U.S. publisher Macmillan Inc. for $2.5
billion and the Official Airline Guides for $750 million last year.
   Maxwell said the company's debt reduction program, which featured
a wide range of asset sales, was nearing completion.
   He said Maxwell Communications had received offers for Maxwell
Graphics, the second largest printing operation in the United
States, and that a deal is expected in the near future.
   In the past year Maxwell Communications dropped its previous
strategy of trying to become an all-round communications group in
favor of becoming one of the world's 10 largest publishing
businesses.
